review_blob: Has hints of carmel, coffee, toffee, chocolate, a complex beer. One of the best brown ales that ive tried.
not a bad beer, nice carbonated with hints of citrus and floral tastes. pours a nice golden orange color with a decent head that stays with the beer.

A great beer, has a lot of taste and not bad with calories. A very easy drinking IPA, a beer you can drink all night long and not have that heavy bloating feeling with some of the heavier beers in this style. It also has a nice balance of hops , you definitely tasty the floral grassy , spruce and some citrus. Pours a beautiful orange amber hue.
A very well balanced triple, has hints bannana, clove that balanced out with a nice hops
Really good triple, pours a nice golden hazy color with a nice head. Has hints of citrus, banana, with a nice balance of malt and hops.
Wow very beer has flavors of raisin, plum, has a nice malty flavor to it also. A lot better then I was expecting, pours a nice creamy head. Actually tastes similar to Rocheford 10

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Great German beer, very malty taste. Has hints of plum raisin and has a very mild aftertaste. Very tasty beer well worth trying
I really liked this beer. Very light, pours a nice golden color. Has a nice clean hoppy aftertaste. Goes down very smoothly.
Actually not that bad!! I was pleasantly surprised by this brew. Pours a deep copper color with a nice head. You can taste the hops, almost has a similar taste to sierra nevada.

Not good at all, doesnt taste like beer at all.
The flavor of blueberry is overpowering almost tastes like a blueberry soda. The blueberry also tastes artifical.
Wow really great beer. Extremely nice pallete. Has hints of plum, raisin, nut , and sweet carmel flavors. Extremely well balanced beer. Very to close to being as  perfect to Westverletren

One  of the best tripels Ive ever tasted to date. Hops and malts are perfectly aligned. Hints of bannana, citrus, apple and plums. Massive head with every pour. Hops have a pine  grassy undertones and are also very complex.No alcohol aftertaste at all. Awesome Brew!!!
Not sure what happened here must gotten a bad bottle, had a sour  aftertaste to  it  with no head to it. I really hope this not what this is supposed to taste like
This stuff is garbage taste like artifical lime in miller lite digusting. No head drink corona instead. Avoid it like the plague
This is a really fantastic beer, very complex in flavor. Nice balance of hops and malt. Has flavors of bananas, figs. and plum. Very complex and delicious.
This beer has a very nice texture. Lots of complex flavors going on in this beer. Hints of bananas, molasses, and spices. Aftertaste is pleasant also. Worth every penny!!
Great holiday beer. The hops really pop out in this beer. Feels like it was brewed with fresh hops that came out of a pine forest. Head is solid, and pours a beautiful amber color.
A underated oktoberfest brew, has a nice balance of  a carmel malt and hops. The head size is nice. Very good
Very good weisse, nicely carbonated. Has a orange haze, with nice hints of fruit.
Very good brew. Beautiful head, pours a nice golden hue, head last a long time Not hugely complex but  a very enjoybable brew.
A true classic, there arent any beers out there as distinctive as guinness. Very well balanced hop and malt tastes. A beautiful beer in apperance and taste.
UPDATED: FEB 29, 2008
One of the best tripels of all time. Pretty much defines what a tripel should taste like. Has a beautiful head ,very full golden bodied beer hints of bananas and raisins. Defines the style perfectly.
Lots of stuff going on with this brew. Hints of caramel, raisins, and plums. Pour a nice deep brown with a frothy head to it.
Very good itallian brew. Almost has a beligian like quality to it. Pallate is complex, has hints of plums,nuts and raisins to. Pours a beautiful redish amber color, with full bodied head.
first russian beer, not too bad . More on the malty side, definitely could use more a hoppy kick to it. Not very complex but a refreshing brew
Nice flavored beligian. Lots of hints of fruit, plums, bannanas, and finishes off with a nice malt aftertaste. Head was a little weak though.
Has a golden haze, with hints of fruits with a slightly hoppy aftertaste. Has a slight alcohol  bite aftertaste but balances out fairly well.
Pours a really dark black. Head is fairly light. Has hints of chocolate, roasted malts, and carmel. Finshes with a fairly sweet somewhat smokey aftertaste.
A really good hefeweizen. Complex flavors with hints of bananas, apples and cloves. Pours a really nice hazy amberish orange color. Reccomended

Not much flavor to this brew, but hey its tastes much better than bud light or coors light. This is probably a good brew to drink if yourre trying to lose weight or have to be the Designated Driver for the night since it has low alcohol.

Pours a very hazy amber color. Beer has a mild hoppy taste to it, also has a very well balanced malty aftertaste to it. The hops in this brew have great flavor, with grassy, pine undertones. Also has hints of citrus in it also. Very good!!
From can. Pours a very light golden color. Has a hoppy aroma to it. Has more of a malty taste to it.  Head is very foamy. Similar to Heineken, only better.
What I really liike about this beer is that it has distinct taste to it. Very malty beer has no bitter hoppy aftertaste to it, has a very heineken quality to it. Tastes really good with Chinese food.
A really soild hefeweizen. Pours a really beautiful orange golden haze. Head is really thick, has nice flowerly hints of clove, banana, and citrus flavor. A great springtime brew.
Very good hefe weizen. Nice banana clove citrus flavor. Head is nice and frothy and thick. Definitely an underated brew.
I actually like this a little better than guinness. It has a much more milder taste than guinness, not as bitter. The head has a beautiful froth to it. Very enjoyable!
This is a great beer, one of my favorites. Pours a golden cloudy haze with a decent.head Tons of citrus flavors in this. Drop an orange in it, double the fun.

Pours a golden hazy hue. More a sweeter taste to with lots of varities of spices. Pours a nice dry finish to. Very easy to drink. Overall great tripel, that is one of the few to actually be offered in 6 packs.
Not a bad beer. Pours a beautiful copper color with a extra foamy head. More on the malty side than hoppy. Head pours nice and fluffy and lasts throughtout the whole drink. Overall great Jersey brew.

The best canned beer out there. It almost looks like cheap crappy beer on surface. Never judge a book by its cover. Pours a nice golden coppery color and leaves plenty of foam. Really hoppy flavor, better than Sierra Nevada in my opinion.
Not a bad beer. Very easy to drink. Has a very hoppy wheaty taste to it. Almost taste like a liquid pretzel. Has a slightly watery taste but a enjoyable brew.
Not a bad ale. Pours a very nice amberish color. Has a evenly balanced hops and malt taste to it. Kinda of on the expensive side though.
Wow what a beautiful beer. Has a nice frothy foamy head poured with a golden haze. Has a very flowery, spicy taste to it almost champagne like. Very easy to drink. One of the best triples out there.
Not a bad beer. Has a nice hop and malt balance to it. Head is a little thin.
Not a bad beer. Much more hops than malt on this brew. Pours a nice amber brown. Head lasts a while on this brew.
beer_name: Saranac Seasons Best Nut Brown Lager

review_blob: A really good beer. Not too hoppy, more on the malty side. Pours a beautiful dark color, with a nice foamy creamy head. You can really taste the roasted carmel flavors in this brew.

I like this beer. Chocolate taste is subtle with a nice malty mild fllavor. It actually blends together really nicely. Not a very bitter tasting beer, light on the hops.Head pours a nice dark brown foamy color. I could see myself drinking this.
I liked this brew had a very malty pleasant taste. Not too hoppy. A very easy drinking beer.

Great stout!! Has an amazing variety of different roasted malt flavors. Almost tastes like coffee, with a chocalate hint.The head on this beer pours a nice medium brown color and has a thick and fluffy texture to it.
